---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const siblingServices = [
  { name: "Invisalign & Clear Aligners", href: "/services/orthodontics/invisalign" },
  { name: "Retainers & Braces", href: "/services/orthodontics/retainers-braces", current: true },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Retainers & Braces Lethbridge | Able Family Dental"
  description="Traditional braces and retainers for orthodontic treatment and retention at Able Family Dental in Lethbridge, AB. Call 403.327.7202 to discuss your options."
>

  <!-- ============================================================
       HERO
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="hidden lg:block absolute right-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-[42%] pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true">
      <img
        src="/images/services/hero-orthodontics.jpg"
        alt=""
        width="800"
        height="600"
        loading="eager"
        decoding="async"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-y-0 left-0 w-2/3" style="background: linear-gradient(to right, var(--color-brand-primary), transparent);"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="container-wide relative py-16 lg:py-24 lg:max-w-[64%]">
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-white mb-5" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/" class="text-white hover:text-white/80 transition-colors">Home</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <a href="/services/" class="text-white/80 hover:text-white transition-colors">Services</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <a href="/services/orthodontics/" class="text-white/80 hover:text-white transition-colors">Orthodontics</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <span class="text-white">Retainers &amp; Braces</span>
      </nav>
      <p class="eyebrow text-white">Orthodontics</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-5xl)] leading-tight text-white max-w-2xl">
        Retainers &amp; Braces
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
        Traditional braces remain one of the most effective tools for correcting alignment and bite concerns. Retainers help preserve the results of orthodontic treatment and prevent teeth from shifting back over time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       MAIN CONTENT + SIDEBAR
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="section-y bg-white">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_300px] gap-12">

        <!-- LEFT: Main content -->
        <div class="space-y-10">

          <!-- Disclaimer -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-surface-cool)] rounded-2xl p-6 border border-[var(--color-border-soft)]">
            <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="white" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">
                Orthodontic services at Able Family Dental are provided by our general dentist team. Our dentists are not licensed specialists in orthodontics. Complex alignment or bite concerns may warrant a referral to an orthodontic specialist.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              Traditional braces
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Traditional metal braces use brackets bonded to the teeth and connected by archwires that apply gentle, consistent pressure to gradually move teeth into a more aligned position. The wire is periodically adjusted over the course of treatment to continue progress.
              </p>
              <p>
                Braces are effective for a broad range of orthodontic concerns, including crowding, spacing, and bite correction. They are a reliable option for patients of various ages and can address cases that may not be suited to removable clear aligner therapy.
              </p>
              <p>
                Treatment duration varies depending on the complexity of the case, but most orthodontic treatment with braces spans one to three years. During this time, regular check-in appointments are needed to monitor progress and adjust the wires.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              Retainers after orthodontic treatment
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Once orthodontic treatment is complete, whether with braces or clear aligners, retainers are essential for maintaining the results. Teeth have a natural tendency to shift back toward their original positions, a process called relapse. Retainers prevent this by holding teeth in their corrected positions while the surrounding bone and tissues stabilise.
              </p>
              <p>
                <strong class="text-[var(--color-brand-primary)]">Removable retainers</strong> are typically worn full-time initially, then transitioned to nighttime wear as directed. They are easy to clean and allow for normal eating and oral hygiene routines.
              </p>
              <p>
                <strong class="text-[var(--color-brand-primary)]">Fixed (bonded) retainers</strong> are thin wires bonded to the back surfaces of the front teeth, keeping them in position without any removable appliance. They are low-maintenance for the patient, though extra care is needed when cleaning around the wire.
              </p>
              <p>
                We discuss retainer options with each patient at the conclusion of active treatment and recommend an approach based on your specific case and lifestyle.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              Who is a candidate?
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Braces may be appropriate for teenagers and adults dealing with crowding, spacing, rotated teeth, or bite concerns. A consultation is the first step to determining whether braces or another orthodontic option is the right fit for your situation.
              </p>
              <p>
                If your needs are beyond what we can address at Able Family Dental, we will be straightforward with you and provide a referral to an orthodontic specialist who is best placed to manage your case.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              Caring for your teeth during treatment
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Oral hygiene is especially important while wearing braces. Brackets and wires create additional surfaces where plaque can accumulate, increasing the risk of decay and gum irritation if cleaning is not thorough. We provide detailed guidance on brushing technique, flossing tools, and dietary choices that protect your teeth throughout treatment.
              </p>
              <p>
                Regular cleanings at our office continue during orthodontic treatment, and we coordinate care to ensure your teeth and gums remain healthy alongside your alignment progress.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- RIGHT: Sidebar -->
        <aside class="space-y-6">

          <!-- Book CTA card -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] rounded-2xl p-6 text-white">
            <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-white">Ready to Book?</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)]">Call us or request an appointment online, new patients welcome.</p>
            <a href="/book/" class="mt-4 btn btn-primary w-full block text-center">Book Appointment</a>
            <a href="/refer/" class="mt-2 btn btn-outline w-full block text-center">Refer Patient</a>
            <a href="tel:+14033277202" class="mt-2 block text-center text-sm text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] hover:text-white transition-colors">403.327.7202</a>
          </div>

          <!-- Sibling services card -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-surface-cool)] rounded-2xl p-6 border border-[var(--color-border-soft)]">
            <h3 class="font-body text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">Orthodontic Services</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              {siblingServices.map(svc => (
                <li>
                  {svc.current ? (
                    <span class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-brand-accent)]">
                      <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-brand-accent)] shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                      {svc.name}
                    </span>
                  ) : (
                    <a href={svc.href} class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] hover:text-[var(--color-brand-accent)] transition-colors">
                      <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-border-soft)] shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                      {svc.name}
                    </a>
                  )}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>

        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       CTA BAND
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] py-16 text-center overflow-hidden relative">
    <svg class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full pointer-events-none" viewBox="0 0 1440 160" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true">
      <path d="M0 60 C 240 20, 480 100, 720 60 C 960 20, 1200 100, 1440 60 L1440 160 L0 160 Z" fill="rgba(255,255,255,0.03)"/>
    </svg>
    <div class="relative container-wide">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-4xl)] text-white leading-tight">Ready to book?</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] text-lg max-w-xl mx-auto">Call <a href="tel:+14033277202" class="text-white font-semibold hover:text-[var(--color-brand-accent-soft)] transition-colors">403.327.7202</a> or request an appointment online.</p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/book/" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Book Appointment</a>
        <a href="/refer/" class="btn btn-lg border border-white/30 text-white hover:bg-white/10 transition-colors">Refer Patient</a>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-lg border border-white/30 text-white hover:bg-white/10 transition-colors">Contact Us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
